Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,opsync,0,0,0,,{opsync}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.92,0:01:35.91,Default,Announcement,825,0,0,,{\q2}The fireworks will begin shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.91,0:01:40.64,Default,Announcement,0,0,0,,We hope everyone is able to join us\Nas we light up the sky.{Please enjoy the glamorous show that \Nwill spread across the night sky.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.64,0:01:43.50,Default,Announcement,0,0,0,,Let's end the cruise with a bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.27,0:01:49.75,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,For now, let's head to the third cargo room, \Nwhere the inflatable boats are stored.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.75,0:01:51.51,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,The director is waiting for us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:54.91,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,We'll lower the boat from \Nthe emergency exit on the second deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.91,0:01:57.01,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Then, we'll have the rendezvous \Nship retrieve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.64,0:02:00.52,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Ideally, this should all happen during the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.90,0:02:00.52,Default,Vides,0,0,0,,{\an8}What should we do with our extra time?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.35,0:02:02.27,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,Wanna watch the fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.27,0:02:05.28,Default,Vides,0,0,0,,Terrible idea. Let's hit up the casino!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.28,0:02:08.39,Default,Vides,0,0,0,,I'm gonna win big and kiss city hall goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.39,0:02:10.23,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,You're gonna piss off the director...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.24,0:02:13.36,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,L-Let's keep our guard up as we proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:14.24,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.57,0:02:21.16,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,{\i1}Blue Lace No. 89 and Mermaid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.51,0:02:23.66,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're both popular perfumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:28.37,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the combination of those two scents, \Nas well as the woman without a scent...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.37,0:02:31.32,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,{\i1}One man, two women, and a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:34.93,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.93,0:02:38.78,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,I love fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.78,0:02:39.83,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.16,0:02:40.43,Alt,Random Boy,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.43,0:02:42.40,Default,Random Boy,0,0,0,,I wanna look over there, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:46.35,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,I can't see with so many people around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.27,0:02:53.99,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,I wonder if we'll see Mommy around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.99,0:02:55.82,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,I really doubt we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.11,0:02:57.40,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}I'm so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.40,0:03:00.68,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}I'm going to propose to my \Ngirlfriend at the finale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:01.58,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't tell if she's here or not\Nwith this much chitter chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:04.79,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}I wonder when I should tell her that she's \Nmore beautiful than the fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:04.79,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll have to listen closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.09,0:03:11.80,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Those people could be assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.15,0:03:14.47,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is there any place we can avoid them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.47,0:03:15.30,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Let's go around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.97,0:03:18.97,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.97,0:03:21.87,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}All the routes to the bow\Nare swarming with enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.36,0:03:24.53,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Of course, I could try brute forcing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.53,0:03:26.32,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}but they might call for backup.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:28.70,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}They could also figure out\Nwhat we're planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:30.28,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Let's head back up to the deck for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.28,0:03:31.23,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:36.04,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,The director gave me a key \Nthat opens the crew corridors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:39.24,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,We'll sneak out using paths \Nunavailable to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:43.68,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I don't sense anyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:46.45,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Everyone's probably distracted by \Nthe event, so we should be fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.45,0:03:48.20,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,but try to make as little noise as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.20,0:03:49.83,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.83,0:03:51.29,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:52.25,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:04.18,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Th-That caught me by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:07.21,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,There, there. They're just fireworks, my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.35,0:04:08.27,Alt,Yor,0,0,0,,We can use the noise as cover. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:18.53,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:22.27,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Hup!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.54,0:04:26.70,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:29.96,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Let's hurry over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:34.46,Default,Sniper,0,0,0,,I see two with black hair. \NIs it the one holding the kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:37.81,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,That's the one. Get the baby while you're at it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:39.83,Default,Sniper,0,0,0,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.25,0:04:49.06,Default,Sniper,0,0,0,,{\i1}She dodged it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.07,0:04:56.91,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, dear... He dodged it.{c: flag}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:14.02,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.02,0:05:16.71,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I-I'm okay... I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.02,0:05:15.03,Alt,Grey,0,0,0,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.06,0:05:28.92,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I didn't feel their presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.92,0:05:30.31,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Whoa, hold on there...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.82,0:05:33.64,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are all skilled assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:43.39,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's no escape. {K: punctuation}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:48.79,Default,Sniper,0,0,0,,You're going first, bitch. This is what you get.{c: i had an edgier idea for this line but he sounds like a fucking twerp}{K: what's the edgier idea? :eyes:}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.88,0:05:59.34,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.34,0:06:02.34,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,I was wondering why you never showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:03.76,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Director!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.76,0:06:06.22,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tch. Guess we have more to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.56,0:06:11.38,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Get to cover, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.38,0:06:13.02,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Hide under that hatch!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.02,0:06:14.23,Default,Chinese Guy,0,0,0,,You're not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.31,0:06:21.69,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Come on, Olka!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:23.06,Default,Scar guy,0,0,0,,Too slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.29,0:06:25.41,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Someone in my blind spot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.71,0:06:33.46,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Zeb!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:42.89,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Zeb!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:48.55,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,That hurt! What a shitty good-for-nothing \Nbulletproof vest!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.24,0:06:48.55,Alt,Olka,0,0,0,,Maybe use your brain next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.98,0:06:50.43,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Nice going, Mr. Grey!
Comment: 0,0:06:50.52,0:06:51.11,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Hi-yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.28,0:07:02.29,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I can finally be at ease \Nknowing they're safe in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:07.24,Default,Bomb Guy,0,0,0,,You think that's enough to stop me? \NI'll blow you to smithereens!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.37,0:07:33.34,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:34.14,Default,Blonde,0,0,0,,Tch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:38.23,Default,Assassin,0,0,0,,Don't poke your body out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.62,0:07:41.02,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,Well, that won't do. The deck is a complete mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.64,0:07:44.78,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,I'll need to make it look like \Nnone of this ever happened.{I'll need to properly sanitize it \Nand get rid of all the evidence.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.54,0:07:56.29,Default,Knife Guy,0,0,0,,You're mine—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.69,0:08:12.32,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,I'd appreciate if you could do this\Nas bloodlessly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.32,0:08:14.27,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,This is {\i1}not{\i0} an easy cleanup.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.27,0:08:16.17,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I didn't notice you made it down here, Director!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.17,0:08:18.37,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry. It completely slipped my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.37,0:08:19.90,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,Well, what's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.19,0:08:22.65,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,We're up against countless trained assassins,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.65,0:08:25.47,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,with unique fighting styles we've\N never seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:27.65,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:31.16,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,They're nothing compared to Garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.21,0:08:34.83,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,They saved us the trouble \Nof having to track them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.83,0:08:36.16,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,Let's purge this filth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.79,0:08:43.93,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Look, now they've turned red!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.93,0:08:47.05,Default,Loud,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't know how you can be equally excited \Nby every single one that goes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:49.85,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.71,0:09:05.63,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,No way, Vides! I hit the jackpot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.09,0:10:06.00,Default,Poison Mist Guy,0,0,0,,{\i1}That was enough poison to take down a bear!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.68,0:10:09.51,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Goodness! You're so rude.{c: flag}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.76,0:10:15.14,Default,Esmeralda,0,0,0,,It is I, Esmerelda! The master of wire—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.99,0:10:18.22,Default,Chakram,0,0,0,,I'm the king of chak—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.99,0:10:24.23,Default,Host,0,0,0,,The fireworks show is about to reach its climax!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:31.53,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,That hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.53,0:10:33.40,Default,Stun gun guy,0,0,0,,Just, "That hurt"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.53,0:11:01.77,Default,Host,0,0,0,,And that concludes our event!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.18,0:11:17.21,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I jammed my finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.72,0:11:30.33,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,Well, damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.33,0:11:34.47,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,You killed every last one of them.\NWhat a terrible person you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.69,0:11:37.88,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Huh? Yes, I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:40.09,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,There wasn't much else I could've done. {K: she should sound more apologetic here, or at least less sassy? maybe "They gave me no other choice."}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:42.14,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Those who point their blade at another
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.14,0:11:44.67,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,cannot complain when they \Nhave one pointed at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:46.77,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,That includes myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.77,0:11:49.27,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,You're so earnest. Well, no matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:51.77,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,This just means I get a \Nbigger cut of the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.21,0:11:53.53,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,It may be too late to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.53,0:11:56.14,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,but could I convince you to walk away from this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.14,0:11:58.35,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,We can still avoid needless bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.35,0:11:59.62,Default,Jogger,0,0,0,,Who do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.62,0:12:01.48,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,That's not going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.48,0:12:03.58,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,We've already received a down payment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.58,0:12:06.79,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,and we're stuck on this boat—much like you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.79,0:12:10.79,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,Also, I suspect he has no intention\Nof letting us leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.79,0:12:12.54,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,You're staring a hole through them, Director!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.20,0:12:17.23,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,War is just another way \Nto get paid to these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.23,0:12:20.57,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,These types only ever cause harm \Nto our country.{If we let them go, they will \Nharm our country somehow.}{taint/pollute idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.57,0:12:23.06,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,Sounds like an old soldier with old ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.06,0:12:26.57,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,You should learn a thing or two \Nfrom the West. Money is power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.57,0:12:28.56,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,Everyone's happy if we're all rich, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.56,0:12:32.69,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,This business requires \Nan adequate amount of foresight.{c: ehhhhh flag}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.69,0:12:36.07,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,You can take some time to self-reflect \Nwhile you're sleeping with the fishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:40.27,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,I don't think {\i1}I'm{\i0} the one who'll end up as fish food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.34,0:12:58.21,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Director!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:14.11,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}My grip strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.11,0:13:15.54,Default,Katana Guy,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.48,0:13:30.38,Default,Katana Guy,0,0,0,,You only postpone the inevitable. Give up.{c: flag}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.96,0:13:33.10,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's on a different level than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.95,0:13:36.32,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}My legs are heavy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.26,0:13:43.53,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,In the event that you get \Nseriously wounded or killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.53,0:13:46.89,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,I will tell the Forgers that you \Nhave been transferred.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.80,0:13:51.39,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I disappeared without saying a word...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.03,0:13:55.40,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}What an awful woman I would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.69,0:14:05.16,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,It'll draw attention \Nif I suddenly have a new hairstyle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:07.72,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Huh? You got a haircut on your trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.72,0:14:10.41,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Well, you see, it's how I dealt \Nwith being turned down! {K: might be a bit vague? consider making this more clearly about the guests "turning down the offer" -- but fine either way}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.83,0:14:14.28,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, now's not the time to \Nbe worrying about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:16.42,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}At this rate, I'm going to be sliced in two!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.18,0:14:30.68,Default,Katana Guy,0,0,0,,If you fear death, I'm afraid \Nit is you who should withdraw, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.68,0:14:33.66,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Th-That isn't happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.66,0:14:36.19,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I won't let you lay a finger \Non Olka or the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:39.50,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,Sucks being at the bottom \Nof the ladder, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.50,0:14:42.79,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,If you'll yield, I wouldn't mind giving you a cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:44.86,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,I'd rather not get hurt anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:46.70,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I don't want a cut! Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:48.27,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,There's nothing ridiculous about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.27,0:14:50.46,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,It's a genuine business proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.46,0:14:54.21,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,You're just like us. \NKilling is what puts food on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.56,0:14:57.13,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Don't compare me to you! I'm—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.52,0:15:01.26,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm doing this to support my family...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.26,0:15:03.17,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I guess that means I {\i0}am{\i1} doing it for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:05.61,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}But... wait, I already make an honest wage. {K: just to clarify, this means "I make an honest wage (from city hall work) already, so I don't really need to kill for money." right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.61,0:15:07.53,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm hunting down bad guys for my country!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.06,0:15:09.72,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}For my country?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:12.91,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Have I always been so righteous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.91,0:15:15.48,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}What am I doing this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.51,0:15:20.50,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, no—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:43.22,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, dear. He might actually \Nkill me. What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.22,0:15:48.09,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now I won't be able to get Loid's \Nshirts from the cleaners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.42,0:15:52.41,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I also won't be able to return \NAnya's library books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.41,0:15:55.10,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wait, what am I even saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.94,0:16:00.11,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why is he pointing a giant sword at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:03.11,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}My head hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.74,0:16:06.14,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I think I'm a bit tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.14,0:16:09.16,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Yor! Hey, Yor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.16,0:16:12.62,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh... Memories of when Yuri was growing up.{"memories of when"/"is that yuri?"}{K: good options, also "getting flashbacks"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.62,0:16:16.91,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yippee! Yor, I just got \Na job offer from foreign affairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.33,0:16:18.12,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, Yuri... I'm so proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.12,0:16:20.22,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,{\an8}I bought you this with my first paycheck!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.50,0:16:21.97,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}You don't need me to support you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.22,0:16:21.12,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\an8}Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.51,0:16:25.25,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't need to kill for a living anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.84,0:16:26.63,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.31,0:16:29.55,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's finish this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.55,0:16:34.14,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, if I die, I won't be able \Nto go to the cleaners or the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.86,0:16:37.67,Default,Katana Guy,0,0,0,,It's over. Finish off Olka and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.67,0:16:38.64,Default,Glasses,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:43.16,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Stop... right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.16,0:16:44.29,Default,Katana Guy,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.29,0:16:45.78,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Olka?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.78,0:16:49.91,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Olka. Why was I acting \Nas her bodyguard again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.13,0:16:53.91,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I just want to live a quiet, peaceful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.91,0:16:59.78,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.32,0:17:05.03,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}The reason I started this job... \Nand continued this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.03,0:17:08.49,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Life had gotten so hectic that \NI had completely forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:12.42,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Was it for the money? For my country?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:15.26,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's only how I justified it.{It was, but it wasn't.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.99,0:17:17.43,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}All I wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:21.44,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}was to protect his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.07,0:17:26.39,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}There are so many \Nneedless tragedies in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.39,0:17:28.07,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}To make sure I don't add to them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.07,0:17:29.89,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}To reduce that number by even one...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.89,0:17:32.21,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have to make the world a beautiful place.{c: i kinda think something about "the world being beautiful" would sound better, dunno if misinterp. I need to thoroughly cleanse this world.}{K: lit. would be beautiful -> peaceful, but either is fine}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.21,0:17:34.22,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}And I stand by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.22,0:17:37.20,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, I have more to lose than ever before.{c: this section was brought to you by vibes :thumbsup: let's hope it isn't too wrong}{K: good tl}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.25,0:17:45.31,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't need peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.22,0:17:48.46,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't care how much blood I've spilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.16,0:17:53.79,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even if my life is constantly on the line...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.35,0:18:03.21,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even if I have to leave the Forgers...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.17,0:18:06.23,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Enduring a merciless job,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.98,0:18:10.56,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,be it for a loved one or for any other reason, \Nrequires an incredible amount of dedication. {K: gjm-kaleido has "be it for a loved one or for any other reason, \Nrequires an incredible amount of dedication."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.56,0:18:12.17,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,And that's something to be proud of.{c: these three lines feel awful but im not lingering on them}{K: also from gjm-kaleido "And that's something to be proud of."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:16.34,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sure Loid would appreciate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:17.74,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}He'd understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:34.26,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have no reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.28,0:18:36.97,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}to give up!{c: ehhhhhhhhhhh}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.97,0:18:36.97,Default,edsync,0,0,0,,{edsync}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:12.50,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,He fled to the back alley!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.50,0:20:14.06,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,Go around and cut him off, Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.06,0:20:14.69,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.55,0:20:29.06,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Yuri?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.06,0:20:30.57,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,Did the suspect get you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.63,0:20:33.96,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Sir... it appears that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.96,0:20:35.82,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.80,0:20:37.93,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,So suddenly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:42.66,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,I've never seen you get sick before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.66,0:20:44.18,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,When I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.06,0:20:48.69,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,When I remember that my sister isn't here,\N my immune system breaks down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.30,0:20:51.76,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,Oh, right. She's on a business \Ntrip right now, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.76,0:20:52.90,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,On that cruise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:55.19,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I let the suspect get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:57.68,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,Just get some rest. \NI'm going to the drug store.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.68,0:20:59.19,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Oh, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.19,0:21:01.82,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Could you also get me some herbal tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.82,0:21:03.49,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,The one with the bear on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.49,0:21:04.65,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:10.96,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whenever I get a cold, \Nit reminds me of when I was a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:14.46,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, no! You have a fever, Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.74,0:21:17.29,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,What should I do? What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:18.94,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me, Yor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.94,0:21:20.97,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,I'll be fine if I get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.23,0:21:23.47,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,First things first, I've gotta get you warm!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:25.49,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,I'll use every blanket we have!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.40,0:21:26.47,Alt,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,That's too many, Yor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.79,0:21:29.24,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Apparently in the east, \Nthey wrap green onions around their necks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.24,0:21:30.98,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,I give! Yor, I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:35.20,Default,Nabor,0,0,0,,Nothing beats herbal tea \Nwith some honey when you're sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.20,0:21:38.23,Default,Nabor,0,0,0,,Try putting elderflower or sage in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.42,0:21:38.89,Alt,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Thanks, Mrs. Nabor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.89,0:21:39.99,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,I'm heading to the mountains now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.26,0:21:41.49,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,I'm home, Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.49,0:21:44.10,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,These should help out with your fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.10,0:21:46.49,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,Yor?! What in the world happened to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.89,0:21:50.10,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,I accidentally made \Nsome bees mad, tee-hee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.10,0:21:51.95,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, and I also fought a boar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.95,0:21:53.33,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Let's make you some hotpot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.38,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,And I'll make you some \Nherbal tea right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.65,0:21:59.63,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't let her hurt herself every time I get sick...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.63,0:22:02.11,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}I need to grow up big and strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.39,0:22:06.05,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get better, Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.05,0:22:08.65,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get better, Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:12.38,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,Hey, Yor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.38,0:22:13.31,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.05,0:22:16.68,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,I'm really glad to be your little brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.18,0:22:23.00,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Goodness, stop talking like you're going to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.61,0:22:24.53,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.41,0:22:30.33,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,I'm glad I have you by my side, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.33,0:22:32.32,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Make sure you take care of yourself{Stay happy and healthy forever}, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.32,0:22:33.04,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,Yor...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.37,0:22:39.25,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}Someone so special shouldn't \Nhave to live in such a cruel world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.19,0:22:43.66,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Drink this! It should help with your cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.66,0:22:45.05,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,I will, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.83,0:22:51.31,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,This sure warms you right up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.31,0:22:52.57,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.57,0:22:54.55,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,There's so much going on\Nin my body right now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.55,0:22:57.84,Default,Young Yuri,0,0,0,,that I'm not worried about my \Ncold symptoms at all anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.33,0:22:59.57,Default,Young Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.02,0:23:05.45,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,You all right? You wouldn't \Nstop moaning in your sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.28,0:23:08.14,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,I bought the stuff you asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.14,0:23:10.11,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.11,0:23:12.95,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,This stuff is famous for tasting awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.43,0:23:15.96,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,It works the best for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:19.78,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,It also tastes the most similar to \Nwhat my sister would make for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.55,0:23:24.18,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,All right! All better!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.18,0:23:25.80,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Let's go catch that suspect!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.80,0:23:28.66,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I'm going to purify the world \Nbefore my sister gets back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.66,0:23:29.93,Default,Lieutenant,0,0,0,,Stay in bed!
